      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Suddenly, even a gradual taper like that could lead to a dangerous rise in your INR, increasing your risk of blood clots or other cardiovascular events. Feeling physically well does not mean your blood clotting levels are stable, and warfarin safety depends entirely on precise lab monitoring rather than how you feel. Because adjusting your dose carries serious health consequences, this decision must wait for your doctor to review your last test results in person.",
      "source": "target",
