      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Self-managing warfarin dosing based solely on internet forums is extremely dangerous because subtle diet changes or minor illnesses can cause sudden, unpredictable spikes in your INR levels. Even a slight increase in clotting risk can lead to catastrophic events like a stroke or internal bleeding without you feeling any symptoms beforehand. Your doctor fills a critical role in interpreting your unique lab data and balancing risks that symptomless feelings or anecdotal advice cannot reveal, so you must continue your current dose until they assess your specific situation.",
      "source": "target",
